-- Foster's Says It's Losing Some Market Share in North America Wine Business
-- B y   R o b e r t   F e n n e r
-- 2010-10-12T03:59:55Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-12/foster-s-says-it-s-losing-some-market-share-in-north-america-wine-business.html
Foster’s Group Ltd.’s Australian
wine head David Dearie said the company is losing some market
share in North America, although it’s from their ‘unprofitable’
segments. The company’s strategy to boost volume in profitable
area won’t change amid recent gains in the Australian dollar,
Dearie told reporters in Melbourne today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Robert Fenner in Melbourne at 
